'''Princess Nakashi''' (? – after 455) was [[Empress of Japan]] as the consort of [[Emperor Ankō]].<ref>https://glim-re.repo.nii.ac.jp/?action=repository_action_common_download&item_id=805&item_no=1&attribute_id=22&file_no=1</ref>
Daughter of Emperor Richū and Kusakanohatabino-hime. Previously married to Prince Ōkusaka, son of Emperor Nintoku. Became a concubine of Emperor Ankō in 454 and was appointed empress 455.
